The intellectual lineage for "dependence-aware corroboration" draws on the
truth-discovery literature, in particular:

  - Yin, Han, Yu (2008). Truth Discovery with Multiple Conflicting Information
    Providers on the Web. IEEE TKDE 20(6).
  - Dong, Berti-Equille, Srivastava (2009). Integrating Conflicting Data:
    The Role of Source Dependence. PVLDB 2(1).
  - Pochampally et al. (2014). Fusing Data with Correlations. SIGMOD 2014.

and the forensic-evidence Bayesian-network tradition (Schum 1994;
Fenton, Neil & Lagnado 2013).

